description:
File: rust/lichen-link/src/link_layer.rs:232-237

The doc comment correctly warns:
    /// Since frames do not include the sender IID, RX must scan peers to find
    /// whose public key verifies the signature. Worst-case is O(n) Schnorr
    /// verifications where n = peer count. Keep peer count low (e.g., <20 direct
    /// neighbors) or implement sender IID hints in upper layers for larger networks.

This is good documentation but the code doesn't enforce the <20 limit or provide any runtime warning when peer count gets high.

Suggestion: Add a compile-time or runtime check that warns when peer count exceeds a threshold (e.g., 20).
